olive oil
1 drizzle white wine vinegar
2 clove garlic
1 packet beef mince
1 packet Ginger & Lemongrass Paste
1 packet fine breadcrumbs
¼ tsp salt
1 packet teriyaki sauce
1 stalk celery
1 bag Slaw Mix
2 radish
1 packet garlic aioli

• Finely chop garlic. Thinly slice celery and radish.
• In a medium bowl, combine garlic, beef mince, ginger & lemongrass paste, fine breadcrumbs, the salt and a pinch of pepper.
• Using damp hands, shape beef mixture into evenly-sized patties (2 per person).

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. When oil is hot, cook patties until just cooked through, 4-5 minutes each side (cook in batches if your pan is getting crowded).
• Add teriyaki sauce and cook, gently turning patties until well coated, 1-2 minutes.

• In a large bowl, add celery, radish, slaw mix and garlic aioli. Add a drizzle of white wine vinegar and olive oil. Toss to combine. Season to taste.

• Divide celery slaw and teriyaki beef patties between plates.
• Spoon any remaining sauce from the pan over patties to serve. Enjoy!